'''Operation Rana Gosa''', (battle cry in Sinhala), was an operation fought during the [[Sri Lankan Civil War]] as part of [[Eelam War III]] launched on 4 March 1999. The Operation resulted in the [[Sri Lankan Army]] re-capturing of 535 square kilometres of territory previously occupied by the [[LTTE]].<ref>http://sundaytimes.lk/990314/sitrep.html</ref>
